{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Let me show you some images"},{"time":1000,"text":"of what I consider to be the cities of tomorrow."},{"time":4000,"text":"So, that's Kibera, the largest squatter community in Nairobi."},{"time":14000,"text":"This is the squatter community in Sanjay Gandhi National Park"},{"time":19000,"text":"in Bombay, India, what's called Mumbai these days."},{"time":23000,"text":"This is Hosinia, the largest and most urbanized favela"},{"time":27000,"text":"in Rio de Janeiro."},{"time":29000,"text":"And this is Sultanbelyi,"},{"time":31000,"text":"which is one of the largest squatter communities in Istanbul."},{"time":38000,"text":"They are what I consider to be the cities of tomorrow,"},{"time":40000,"text":"the new urban world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"Now, why do I say that?"},{"time":44000,"text":"To tell you about that I have to talk about this fellow here,"},{"time":47000,"text":"his name is Julius."},{"time":49000,"text":"And I met Julius the last week that I was living in Kibera."},{"time":54000,"text":"So, I had been there almost three months,"},{"time":57000,"text":"and I was touring around the city going to different squatter areas"},{"time":61000,"text":"and Julius was tagging along, and he was bug eyed"},{"time":64000,"text":"and at certain points we were walking around,"},{"time":67000,"text":"he grabbed my hand for support,"},{"time":69000,"text":"which is something most Kenyans would never consider doing."},{"time":72000,"text":"They're very polite and they don't get so forward so quickly."},{"time":77000,"text":"And I found out later that it was Julius' first day in Nairobi,"},{"time":83000,"text":"and he's one of many."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"So, close to 200,000 people a day"},{"time":91000,"text":"migrate from the rural to the urban areas."},{"time":95000,"text":"That's, and I'm going to be fair to the statisticians"},{"time":98000,"text":"who talked this morning, not almost 1.5 million people a week,"},{"time":101000,"text":"but almost 1.4 million people a week but I'm a journalist,"},{"time":104000,"text":"and we exaggerate, so almost 1.5 million people a week,"},{"time":108000,"text":"close to 70 million people a year."},{"time":112000,"text":"And if you do the math, that's 130 people every minute."},{"time":116000,"text":"So, that'll be -- in the 18 minutes that I'm given to talk here,"},{"time":119000,"text":"between two and three thousand people will have journeyed to the cities."},{"time":123000,"text":"And here are the statistics."},{"time":126000,"text":"Today -- a billion squatters,"},{"time":128000,"text":"one in six people on the planet."},{"time":130000,"text":"2030 -- two billion squatters,"},{"time":133000,"text":"one in four people on the planet."},{"time":135000,"text":"And the estimate is that in 2050, there'll be three billion squatters,"},{"time":138000,"text":"better than one in three people on earth."},{"time":142000,"text":"So, these are the cities of the future, and we have to engage them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151000,"text":"And I was thinking this morning of the good life,"},{"time":157000,"text":"and before I show you the rest of my presentation,"},{"time":159000,"text":"I'm going to violate TED rules here,"},{"time":161000,"text":"and I'm going to read you something from my book as quickly as I can."},{"time":167000,"text":"Because I think it says something about reversing our perception"},{"time":172000,"text":"of what we think the good life is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"So -- \"The hut was made of corrugated metal, set on a concrete pad."},{"time":184000,"text":"It was a 10 by 10 cell."},{"time":187000,"text":"Armstrong O'Brian, Jr. shared it with three other men."},{"time":191000,"text":"Armstrong and his friends had no water --"},{"time":194000,"text":"they bought it from a nearby tap owner --"},{"time":196000,"text":"no toilet -- the families in this compound shared a single pit-latrine --"},{"time":201000,"text":"and no sewers or sanitation."},{"time":203000,"text":"They did have electricity,"},{"time":205000,"text":"but it was illegal service tapped from someone else's wires,"},{"time":208000,"text":"and could only power one feeble bulb."},{"time":211000,"text":"This was Southland, a small shanty community"},{"time":214000,"text":"on the western side of Nairobi, Kenya."},{"time":216000,"text":"But it could've been anywhere in the city,"},{"time":219000,"text":"because more than half the city of Nairobi lives like this."},{"time":222000,"text":"1.5 million people stuffed into mud or metal huts"},{"time":226000,"text":"with no services, no toilets, no rights."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"\"Armstrong explained the brutal reality of their situation:"},{"time":233000,"text":"they paid 1,500 shillings in rent, about 20 bucks a month,"},{"time":236000,"text":"a relatively high price for a Kenyan shantytown,"},{"time":239000,"text":"and they could not afford to be late with the money."},{"time":242000,"text":"'In case you owe one month, the landlord will come with his henchmen"},{"time":244000,"text":"and bundle you out. He will confiscate your things,' Armstrong said."},{"time":248000,"text":"'Not one month, one day,' his roommate Hilary Kibagendi Onsomu,"},{"time":253000,"text":"who was cooking ugali, the spongy white cornmeal concoction"},{"time":256000,"text":"that is the staple food in the country, cut into the conversation."},{"time":260000,"text":"They called their landlord a Wabenzi, meaning that he is a person"},{"time":263000,"text":"who has enough money to drive a Mercedes-Benz."},{"time":269000,"text":"Hilary served the ugali with a fry of meat and tomatoes;"},{"time":272000,"text":"the sun slammed down on the thin steel roof;"},{"time":275000,"text":"and we perspired as we ate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277000,"text":"\"After we finished, Armstrong straightened his tie,"},{"time":280000,"text":"put on a wool sports jacket, and we headed out into the glare."},{"time":284000,"text":"Outside a mound of garbage formed the border"},{"time":287000,"text":"between Southland and the adjacent legal neighborhood of Langata."},{"time":290000,"text":"It was perhaps eight feet tall, 40 feet long, and 10 feet wide."},{"time":295000,"text":"And it was set in a wider watery ooze."},{"time":299000,"text":"As we passed, two boys were climbing the mount Kenya of trash."},{"time":303000,"text":"They couldn't have been more than five or six years old."},{"time":305000,"text":"They were barefoot, and with each step their toes sank into the muck"},{"time":309000,"text":"sending hundreds of flies scattering from the rancid pile."},{"time":313000,"text":"I thought they might be playing King of the Hill, but I was wrong."},{"time":317000,"text":"Once atop the pile, one of the boys lowered his shorts,"},{"time":321000,"text":"squatted, and defecated."},{"time":323000,"text":"The flies buzzed hungrily around his legs."},{"time":327000,"text":"When 20 families -- 100 people or so -- share a single latrine,"},{"time":332000,"text":"a boy pooping on a garbage pile is perhaps no big thing."},{"time":336000,"text":"But it stood in jarring contrast"},{"time":338000,"text":"to something Armstrong had said as we were eating --"},{"time":341000,"text":"that he treasured the quality of life in his neighborhood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"\"For Armstrong, Southland wasn't constrained by its material conditions."},{"time":349000,"text":"Instead, the human spirit radiated out"},{"time":352000,"text":"from the metal walls and garbage heaps to offer something"},{"time":355000,"text":"no legal neighborhood could: freedom."},{"time":358000,"text":"'This place is very addictive,' he had said."},{"time":361000,"text":"'It's a simple life, but nobody is restricting you."},{"time":364000,"text":"Nobody is controlling what you do."},{"time":367000,"text":"Once you have stayed here, you cannot go back.'"},{"time":371000,"text":"He meant back beyond that mountain of trash,"},{"time":373000,"text":"back in the legal city, of legal buildings,"},{"time":376000,"text":"with legal leases and legal rights."},{"time":379000,"text":"'Once you have stayed here,' he said,"},{"time":382000,"text":"'you can stay for the rest of your life.'\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"So, he has hope, and this is where these communities start."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391000,"text":"This is perhaps the most primitive shanty that you can find in Kibera,"},{"time":396000,"text":"little more than a stick-and-mud hut next to a garbage heap."},{"time":401000,"text":"This is getting ready for the monsoon in Bombay, India."},{"time":404000,"text":"This is home improvement:"},{"time":406000,"text":"putting plastic tarps on your roof."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"This is in Rio de Janeiro, and it's getting a bit better, right?"},{"time":414000,"text":"We're seeing scavenged terra cotta tile and little pieces of signs,"},{"time":420000,"text":"and plaster over the brick, some color,"},{"time":423000,"text":"and this is Sulay Montakaya's house in Sultanbelyi, and it's getting even better."},{"time":428000,"text":"He's got a fence; he scavenged a door;"},{"time":430000,"text":"he's got new tile on the roof."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433000,"text":"And then you get Rocinha"},{"time":435000,"text":"and you can see that it's getting even better."},{"time":439000,"text":"The buildings here are multi-story."},{"time":441000,"text":"They develop -- you can see on the far right"},{"time":444000,"text":"one where it seems to just stack on top of each other,"},{"time":447000,"text":"room, after room, after room."},{"time":449000,"text":"And what people do is they develop their home on one or two stories,"},{"time":453000,"text":"and they sell their loggia or roof rights,"},{"time":456000,"text":"and someone else builds on top of their building,"},{"time":457000,"text":"and then that person sells the roof rights,"},{"time":459000,"text":"and someone else builds on top of their building."},{"time":461000,"text":"All of these buildings are made out of reinforced concrete and brick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465000,"text":"And then you get Sultanbelyi, in Turkey, where it's even built"},{"time":469000,"text":"to a higher level of design."},{"time":470000,"text":"The crud in the front is mattress stuffing,"},{"time":473000,"text":"and you see that all over Turkey."},{"time":475000,"text":"People dry out or air out their mattress stuffing on their roofs."},{"time":479000,"text":"But the green building, on behind,"},{"time":481000,"text":"you can see that the top floor is not occupied,"},{"time":483000,"text":"so people are building with the possibility of expansion."},{"time":486000,"text":"And it's built to a pretty high standard of design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489000,"text":"And then you finally get squatter homes like this,"},{"time":491000,"text":"which is built on the suburban model."},{"time":493000,"text":"Hey, that's a single family home in the squatter community."},{"time":496000,"text":"That's also in Istanbul, Turkey."},{"time":498000,"text":"They're quite vital places, these communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500000,"text":"This is the main drag of Rocinha, the Estrada da Gavea,"},{"time":504000,"text":"and there's a bus route that runs through it,"},{"time":506000,"text":"lots of people out on the street."},{"time":508000,"text":"These communities in these cities are actually more vital"},{"time":511000,"text":"than the illegal communities."},{"time":513000,"text":"They have more things going on in them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516000,"text":"This is a typical pathway in Rocinha called a \"beco\" --"},{"time":519000,"text":"these are how you get around the community."},{"time":521000,"text":"It's on very steep ground."},{"time":523000,"text":"They're built on the hills, inland from the beaches in Rio,"},{"time":526000,"text":"and you can see that the houses are just cantilevered over the natural obstructions."},{"time":530000,"text":"So, that's just a rock in the hillside."},{"time":532000,"text":"And these becos are normally very crowded,"},{"time":536000,"text":"and people hump furniture up them, or refrigerators up them,"},{"time":539000,"text":"all sorts of things."},{"time":541000,"text":"Beer is all carried in on your shoulders."},{"time":543000,"text":"Beer is a very important thing in Brazil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546000,"text":"This is commerce in Kenya, right along the train tracks,"},{"time":551000,"text":"so close to the train tracks that the merchants"},{"time":553000,"text":"sometimes have to pull the merchandise out of the way."},{"time":556000,"text":"This is a marketplace, also in Kenya, Toi Market,"},{"time":559000,"text":"lots of dealers, in almost everything you want to buy."},{"time":563000,"text":"Those green things in the foreground are mangoes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566000,"text":"This is a shopping street in Kibera,"},{"time":568000,"text":"and you can see that there's a soda dealer, a health clinic,"},{"time":573000,"text":"two beauty salons, a bar, two grocery stores, and a church, and more."},{"time":578000,"text":"It's a typical downtown street; it just happens to be self-built."},{"time":583000,"text":"This here, on the right-hand side,"},{"time":586000,"text":"is what's called a -- if you look at the fine print under the awning --"},{"time":589000,"text":"it's a hotel."},{"time":591000,"text":"And what hotel means, in Kenya and India, is an eating-place."},{"time":597000,"text":"So, that's a restaurant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599000,"text":"People steal electrical power -- this is Rio."},{"time":601000,"text":"People tap in and they have thieves who are called \"grillos\" or \"crickets,\""},{"time":608000,"text":"and they steal the electrical power"},{"time":610000,"text":"and wire the neighborhood."},{"time":612000,"text":"People burn trash to get rid of the garbage,"},{"time":615000,"text":"and they dig their own sewer channels."},{"time":619000,"text":"Talk about more plastic bags than plankton."},{"time":622000,"text":"And sometimes they have natural trash-disposal."},{"time":626000,"text":"And when they have more money they cement their streets,"},{"time":629000,"text":"and they put in sewers and good water pipes, and stuff like that."},{"time":633000,"text":"This is water going to Rio. People run their water pipes all over the place,"},{"time":639000,"text":"and that little hut right there has a pump in it, and that's what people do:"},{"time":642000,"text":"they steal electricity; they install a pump"},{"time":644000,"text":"and they tap into the water main, and pump water up to their houses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648000,"text":"So, the question is how do you go from the mud-hut village,"},{"time":654000,"text":"to the more developed city, to the even highly developed Sultanbelyi?"},{"time":659000,"text":"I say there are two things."},{"time":661000,"text":"One is people need a guarantee they won't be evicted."},{"time":663000,"text":"That does not necessarily mean property rights,"},{"time":665000,"text":"and I would disagree with Hernando de Soto on that question,"},{"time":669000,"text":"because property rights create a lot of complications."},{"time":671000,"text":"They're most often sold to people, and people then wind up in debt"},{"time":675000,"text":"and have to pay back the debt,"},{"time":677000,"text":"and sometimes have to sell their property"},{"time":679000,"text":"in order to pay back the debt."},{"time":681000,"text":"There's a whole variety of other reasons why property rights"},{"time":683000,"text":"sometimes don't work in these cases,"},{"time":685000,"text":"but they do need security of tenure."},{"time":687000,"text":"And they need access to politics, and that can mean two things."},{"time":691000,"text":"That can mean community organizing from below,"},{"time":695000,"text":"but it can also mean possibilities from above."},{"time":698000,"text":"And I say that because the system in Turkey is notable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703000,"text":"Turkey has two great laws that protect squatters."},{"time":705000,"text":"One is that -- it's called \"gecekondu\" in Turkish,"},{"time":708000,"text":"which means \"built overnight,\" and if you build your house overnight"},{"time":712000,"text":"in Turkey, you can't be evicted without due process of law,"},{"time":716000,"text":"if they don't catch you during the night."},{"time":719000,"text":"And the second aspect is that once you have 2,000 people"},{"time":723000,"text":"in the community, you can petition the government"},{"time":725000,"text":"to be recognized as a legal sub-municipality."},{"time":729000,"text":"And when you're a legal sub-municipality, you suddenly have politics."},{"time":732000,"text":"You're allowed to have an elected government, collect taxes,"},{"time":734000,"text":"provide municipal services, and that's exactly what they do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"So, these are the civic leaders of the future."},{"time":742000,"text":"The woman in the center is Geeta Jiwa."},{"time":743000,"text":"She lives in one of those tents on the highway median in Mumbai."},{"time":749000,"text":"That's Sureka Gundi; she also lives with her family"},{"time":751000,"text":"on the tent along the same highway median."},{"time":753000,"text":"They're very outspoken. They're very active."},{"time":755000,"text":"They can be community leaders."},{"time":758000,"text":"This woman is Nine, which means \"grandma\" in Turkish."},{"time":761000,"text":"And there were three old ladies who lived in --"},{"time":763000,"text":"that's her self-built house behind her -- and they've lived there for 30 or 40 years,"},{"time":768000,"text":"and they are the backbone of the community there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771000,"text":"This is Richard Muthama Peter,"},{"time":773000,"text":"and he is an itinerant street photographer in Kibera."},{"time":776000,"text":"He makes money taking pictures of the neighborhood,"},{"time":779000,"text":"and the people in the neighborhood,"},{"time":781000,"text":"and is a great resource in the community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"And finally my choice to run for mayor of Rio is Cezinio,"},{"time":787000,"text":"the fruit merchant with his two kids here,"},{"time":789000,"text":"and a more honest and giving and caring man I don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794000,"text":"The future of these communities is in the people"},{"time":796000,"text":"and in our ability to work with those people."},{"time":800000,"text":"So, I think the message I take, from what I read from the book,"},{"time":804000,"text":"from what Armstrong said, and from all these people,"},{"time":806000,"text":"is that these are neighborhoods."},{"time":808000,"text":"The issue is not urban poverty."},{"time":810000,"text":"The issue is not the larger, over-arching thing."},{"time":813000,"text":"The issue is for us to recognize that these are neighborhoods --"},{"time":816000,"text":"this is a legitimate form of urban development --"},{"time":819000,"text":"and that cities have to engage these residents,"},{"time":822000,"text":"because they are building the cities of the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}